HEADWORD: Erlking
<hw>Erl"king`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G.
<ets>erlk⟦oum⟧nig</ets>, fr. Dan. <ets>ellekonge</ets> elfking.]</ety>
<def>A personification, in German and Scandinavian mythology, of a
spirit or natural power supposed to work mischief and ruin, esp. to
children.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

